structure.unit: Chapter 17C METROPOLITAN DADE COUNTY DEMOLITION OF MOBILE HOMES AND REMOVAL OF DEBRIS FROM MOBILE HOME PARKS RENDERED UNINHABITABLE BY HURRICANE ANDREW AFTER ITS AFTERMATH

text.section: The provisions of this chapter shall be cumulative and supplemental to and not in derogation of any provisions of the Florida Statutes, the Code of Metropolitan Dade County or any other applicable law.
